energy agency inspectors back to north korea is not necessarily a good idea inspectors would almost certainly have access to only some north korean nuclear facilities he contended while others would remain hidden and north korea would use the presence of the international inspectors to try to give the international community the impression that their nuclear program is legitimate the full text of the korean language interview is available on the voa korean service website and the full audio is on itunes voa korean evening broadcast jan 3 2011 minute 13 09 to minute 22 19 voa korean service new year interview david straub former state department korea director prospects for north korean nuclear negotiations in the new year korean search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest straub addresses abrupt change in north korea agreement march 16 2012 shorenstein aparc ksp news straub on us north korea nuclear agreement march 1 2012 shorenstein aparc ksp news two koreas unlikely to head into armed clash says shorenstein aparc's david straub shorenstein aparc ksp in the news korea times english edition on may 26 2010 north korea and the sinking of the south korean navy vessel cheonan may 19 2010 shorenstein aparc ksp news north korea says it is in final stage of uranium enrichment cisac in the news washington post on september 4 2009 david straub joins clinton delegation to north korea to secure release of current tv journalists august 10 2009 fsi stanford shorenstein aparc ksp in the news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
